# Ninjix authored demo timeline.
# Times can be written as seconds; the runtime converts them to 60 Hz ticks.
# `move dx dy during t` emits smooth relative PS/2 mouse packets.

at 0.2s caption top 3s NINJIX LEVEL 1
at 0.8s key ENTER down
at 0.9s key ENTER up

at 1.5s caption 3s PLACE A BASIC TOWER NEAR THE FIRST TURN
at 1.8s key 1 down
at 1.9s key 1 up
at 2.0s move -192 220 during 1.2s
at 3.4s mouse 0 0 1
at 3.5s mouse 0 0 0

at 4.5s caption 3s ADD SLOWING SUPPORT FOR THE LONG LANE
at 4.8s key 3 down
at 4.9s key 3 up
at 5.0s move 128 -96 during 1.1s
at 6.3s mouse 0 0 1
at 6.4s mouse 0 0 0

at 7.4s caption 3s START THE FIRST WAVE
at 7.6s move 314 -390 during 1.8s
at 9.6s mouse 0 0 1
at 9.7s mouse 0 0 0

at 12s caption 4s LET THE TOWERS WORK
at 18s mouse 0 0 1
at 18.1s mouse 0 0 0

at 24s caption 2s CUTTING A QUIET WAIT
at 26s capture out
at 26.2s key N down
at 26.3s key N up
at 30s capture in
at 30.2s caption bottom 4s LEVEL 2 STARTS AFTER THE CAPTURE CUT

at 35s key 1 down
at 35.1s key 1 up
at 35.2s move -250 170 during 1.8s
at 37.2s mouse 0 0 1
at 37.3s mouse 0 0 0

at 45s caption 5s RECORDED SCRIPTS CAN BECOME BUG REPORTS
at 58s key ESC down
at 58.1s key ESC up
at 58.3s key DOWN down
at 58.4s key DOWN up
at 58.6s key ENTER down
at 58.7s key ENTER up
at 59s key ESC down
at 59.1s key ESC up
